        <num>CCP 1920</num>
        <heading>1920.  Costs; parties liable; procedure for taxing</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1920.  Costs; parties liable; procedure for taxing
Unless the judgment provides otherwise, costs shall be paid by the party cast, and may be taxed by a rule to show cause.
Except as otherwise provided by law, the court may render judgment for costs, or any part thereof, against any party, as it may consider equitable.</p>
        </content>
